{
  "texts": [
    "Their proof generalizes mutatis mutandis.",
    "Lemma 4.1 ([36]).",
    "For any finite region C, the map πC 1: H C 1 → A(Σ C 1) is an isomorphism of vector spaces.",
    "Convention 4.2.",
    "We will freely use the isomorphism π C 1 to represent states in H C 1 by string diagrams on Σ C 1, where we can use the graphical calculus."
  ]
}